## Summary
Implemented a lightweight keyword-matching knowledge retrieval system using pure JavaScript with no external dependencies. The solution extracts structured content from `knowledge/*.md` files (Summary, Key Points, Tags), scores relevance via keyword overlap, and returns cleaned excerpts for context assembly. The `load_context.js` integration adds relevant knowledge chunks to the context packet before task execution, with clear logging for transparency. All files are processed synchronously with strict adherence to the 800-character excerpt limit and 10% relevance threshold.
